US commercial flights analysis - Summary report

Introduction

Analyzig the data from Research and Innovative Technology Administration (RITA) we were able to answer the following questions:

  1. How is the trend of commercial flights in the US?

  2. Which is the best (worst) day of the week to take a flight?

  3. Which is the best (worst) season to flight in terms of delay?

Results

The insight we found are:

  1. The trend of commercial flights in the USA as a number of flights seems to grow year by year, even though in a non-linear way.

  1. The best day of the week to fly which minimize the probability of having a dalayed flight is Saturday with an average of percentage of delayed flights that moves from 30% to 52%. The warse day of the week are both Friday and Thursday with an avareges of percentage of delayed flights that moves respectively between 40% and 62% (Friday) and 39% and 63% (Thursday).

  1. The best season to fly to minimize the probability of having a dalayed flight is Fall with an average of percentage of delayed flights that goes from 29% to 57%. The worst seasons, instead, are Summer and Winter with an avareges of percentage of delayed flights that moves respectively between 36% and 63% (Summer) and 33% and 66% (Winter).
